00:07:27.350 --> 00:07:30.410 align:middle line:10%
been in for lab
tests or something,

00:07:30.410 --> 00:07:32.330 align:middle line:10%
we don't tend to
think about what's

00:07:32.330 --> 00:07:34.700 align:middle line:10%
encased behind skin and bones.

00:07:34.700 --> 00:07:40.620 align:middle line:84%
But that is-- if we were looking
at it as an entity of its own,

00:07:40.620 --> 00:07:41.420 align:middle line:90%
which they are.

00:07:41.420 --> 00:07:42.140 align:middle line:90%
The organs are.

00:07:42.140 --> 00:07:44.550 align:middle line:10%
If you look at it from more
of an esoteric point of view,

00:07:44.550 --> 00:07:46.550 align:middle line:10%
they're very much
their own entities

00:07:46.550 --> 00:07:49.610 align:middle line:10%
with their own mind, their
own information systems

00:07:49.610 --> 00:07:50.900 align:middle line:10%
and means of communicating.

00:07:50.900 --> 00:07:53.030 align:middle line:10%
How would you
characterize the adrenals

00:07:53.030 --> 00:07:55.010 align:middle line:10%
as an independent member
of your community?

00:07:55.010 --> 00:07:57.410 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:07:57.410 --> 00:08:01.220 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Well, they're
the glands of boldness,

00:08:01.220 --> 00:08:03.860 align:middle line:90%
and courage, and strength.

00:08:03.860 --> 00:08:06.680 align:middle line:84%
They can also be, though,
the glands of fear,

00:08:06.680 --> 00:08:11.510 align:middle line:84%
and self degradation,
and depression.

00:08:11.510 --> 00:08:15.800 align:middle line:84%
But, hopefully, we're a
happy mix of all that.

00:08:15.800 --> 00:08:18.020 align:middle line:10%
And, again, we have
to honor the fact

00:08:18.020 --> 00:08:22.070 align:middle line:10%
that they do need
nutrients, and they do need

00:08:22.070 --> 00:08:23.510 align:middle line:10%
mental emotional balancing--

00:08:23.510 --> 00:08:25.610 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Care
and consideration,

00:08:25.610 --> 00:08:27.590 align:middle line:10%
just like we do as a whole.

00:08:27.590 --> 00:08:29.390 align:middle line:10%
Let's talk about some
of the hormones that

00:08:29.390 --> 00:08:32.570 align:middle line:10%
are depleted when we get into
more of the self-deprecating

00:08:32.570 --> 00:08:36.650 align:middle line:10%
and fear end of the use
of our educational glands,

00:08:36.650 --> 00:08:39.710 align:middle line:10%
and they start becoming
out of balance.

00:08:39.710 --> 00:08:43.039 align:middle line:84%
What is the cascade effect
in the sex hormones?

00:08:43.039 --> 00:08:46.310 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Well, you see, the
important thing to remember

00:08:46.310 --> 00:08:49.980 align:middle line:84%
is that all hormones
start with cholesterol.

00:08:49.980 --> 00:08:53.210 align:middle line:84%
And, in other words, the
steroid hormones-- steroids

00:08:53.210 --> 00:08:55.400 align:middle line:90%
means from fat or from lipid.

00:08:55.400 --> 00:08:58.220 align:middle line:84%
And so, cholesterol
is the building block.

00:08:58.220 --> 00:09:01.460 align:middle line:84%
And from there, you go in
to pregnenolone, and then

00:09:01.460 --> 00:09:04.040 align:middle line:84%
progesterone, and I won't go
through the whole pathway,

00:09:04.040 --> 00:09:09.170 align:middle line:84%
but suffice it to say that
the adrenal glands make

00:09:09.170 --> 00:09:12.470 align:middle line:84%
the adrenal hormones, the
stress hormones, cortisol, DHA,

00:09:12.470 --> 00:09:15.230 align:middle line:84%
and adrenaline, and
such, but they also

00:09:15.230 --> 00:09:17.090 align:middle line:90%
make the sex hormones.

00:09:17.090 --> 00:09:19.550 align:middle line:10%
And one of the problems
that occurs, especially

00:09:19.550 --> 00:09:22.640 align:middle line:10%
after a person has
years of stress,

00:09:22.640 --> 00:09:27.350 align:middle line:10%
is that their adrenal glands
get taxed, tapped out,

00:09:27.350 --> 00:09:32.510 align:middle line:10%
and then they're less able to
be the backup system for the sex

00:09:32.510 --> 00:09:36.920 align:middle line:10%
hormone production,
which we sorely rely on

00:09:36.920 --> 00:09:41.120 align:middle line:10%
in middle age, when the sex
hormones begin to decline,

00:09:41.120 --> 00:09:44.570 align:middle line:10%
estrogen, progesterone, and
testosterone begin to decline,

00:09:44.570 --> 00:09:48.270 align:middle line:10%
and the body wants the
adrenal glands to kick in.

00:09:48.270 --> 00:09:50.520 align:middle line:84%
And the adrenal glands say,
hey, what are you kidding?

00:09:50.520 --> 00:09:51.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I'm worn out.

00:09:51.180 --> 00:09:51.950 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah.

00:09:51.950 --> 00:09:53.480 align:middle line:84%
You're not getting
anything from me.

00:09:53.480 --> 00:09:53.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:09:53.780 --> 00:09:55.140 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: You got
to treat me right.

00:09:55.140 --> 00:09:55.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:09:55.640 --> 00:09:56.550 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:09:56.550 --> 00:09:59.787 align:middle line:10%
Well, you can say that the horse
has already bolted on that one

00:09:59.787 --> 00:10:02.120 align:middle line:10%
if you've been treating your
body in a rough fashion all

00:10:02.120 --> 00:10:02.920 align:middle line:10%
those years.

00:10:02.920 --> 00:10:03.890 align:middle line:10%
How does that impact--

00:10:03.890 --> 00:10:04.970 align:middle line:10%
you're talking
about what happens

00:10:04.970 --> 00:10:07.160 align:middle line:10%
when we go through our
middle years and menopause,

00:10:07.160 --> 00:10:09.650 align:middle line:10%
but what happens in
the younger years,

00:10:09.650 --> 00:10:12.500 align:middle line:10%
let's say for women
and men, actually both,

00:10:12.500 --> 00:10:14.135 align:middle line:10%
when it comes to fertility?

00:10:14.135 --> 00:10:16.760 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Oh boy.

00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:21.310 align:middle line:84%
So sad, today, the
fertility issues.

00:10:21.310 --> 00:10:26.040 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think that we're
dealing with a severe fertility

00:10:26.040 --> 00:10:29.460 align:middle line:84%
problems because of the
environmental chemicals,

00:10:29.460 --> 00:10:32.220 align:middle line:84%
which have an estrogen
effect in the body, which

00:10:32.220 --> 00:10:38.070 align:middle line:84%
affects both boys and girls,
teens and young adults.

00:10:38.070 --> 00:10:41.490 align:middle line:84%
And we also have
hormone replacements

00:10:41.490 --> 00:10:43.300 align:middle line:90%
and in the birth control pill.

00:10:43.300 --> 00:10:44.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right

00:10:44.100 --> 00:10:48.270 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: And we have
steroid use among teenage boys,

00:10:48.270 --> 00:10:51.900 align:middle line:90%
and young adult men, athletes.

00:10:51.900 --> 00:10:54.240 align:middle line:84%
And all of these affect
the hormone balance,

00:10:54.240 --> 00:10:57.160 align:middle line:84%
and all of these can throw
off the sex hormones.

00:10:57.160 --> 00:10:58.890 align:middle line:84%
And so, I think
that the fertility

00:10:58.890 --> 00:11:07.800 align:middle line:84%
issue is it can be not only
affected, but can be remedied.

00:11:07.800 --> 00:11:09.720 align:middle line:90%
But all of these other--

00:11:09.720 --> 00:11:12.270 align:middle line:84%
all these aggravators
have to be handled.

00:11:12.270 --> 00:11:15.000 align:middle line:84%
And like, for instance, when I
get a girl that comes into me,

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:18.330 align:middle line:84%
and she's coming to deal
with her blood sugar

00:11:18.330 --> 00:11:20.610 align:middle line:84%
problems, or her
depression, or her PMS,

00:11:20.610 --> 00:11:22.830 align:middle line:84%
and her parents
wanted to see me.

00:11:22.830 --> 00:11:25.830 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, she's most the
time on the birth control pill.

00:11:25.830 --> 00:11:30.000 align:middle line:84%
I always do my due
diligence to talk to them

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:34.110 align:middle line:84%
about why they shouldn't
be on birth control pill.

00:11:34.110 --> 00:11:39.680 align:middle line:84%
And the what occurs is, that
most of the time I'm able to, I

00:11:39.680 --> 00:11:42.173 align:middle line:84%
guess, get the fear into
them enough where they're--

00:11:42.173 --> 00:11:43.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And so what?

00:11:43.090 --> 00:11:44.998 align:middle line:84%
So, let's say you're
the mother of a teenage,

00:11:44.998 --> 00:11:47.040 align:middle line:84%
or you're a teenage girl
watching this right now.

00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:48.582 align:middle line:84%
What's the lecture,
you would deliver

00:11:48.582 --> 00:11:50.130 align:middle line:90%
regarding birth control?

00:11:50.130 --> 00:11:51.972 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah,
so I would say, do--

00:11:51.972 --> 00:11:53.430 align:middle line:84%
the birth control
pill is basically

00:11:53.430 --> 00:11:54.900 align:middle line:90%
controlling the hormone system.

00:11:54.900 --> 00:11:58.110 align:middle line:84%
It's basically telling
the body you're pregnant.

00:11:58.110 --> 00:12:01.450 align:middle line:84%
And then, you stay on the
pill for 10 years, 15 years,

00:12:01.450 --> 00:12:04.800 align:middle line:84%
20 years, and then you decide
you want to get pregnant,

00:12:04.800 --> 00:12:07.290 align:middle line:84%
and you go off the pill,
but the body's already

00:12:07.290 --> 00:12:08.898 align:middle line:90%
been pregnant in a sense.

00:12:08.898 --> 00:12:10.440 align:middle line:84%
In other words, the
feedback system--

00:12:10.440 --> 00:12:11.315 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Repeatedly.

00:12:11.315 --> 00:12:15.420 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Is telling you
that it's in a certain state.

00:12:15.420 --> 00:12:19.440 align:middle line:84%
And then, all of a sudden
you want it to perform and it

00:12:19.440 --> 00:12:21.000 align:middle line:90%
can't.

00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:23.940 align:middle line:84%
On top of all that, you get all
the toxins from the estrogen

00:12:23.940 --> 00:12:26.370 align:middle line:84%
and progesterone residues
from the birth control pill,

00:12:26.370 --> 00:12:29.070 align:middle line:84%
and the toxification
of the liver,

00:12:29.070 --> 00:12:33.330 align:middle line:84%
and all kinds of other
issues that occur when

00:12:33.330 --> 00:12:35.960 align:middle line:90%
the body has chemical control.

00:12:35.960 --> 00:12:37.710 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: So, essentially,
you'd recommend

00:12:37.710 --> 00:12:41.740 align:middle line:10%
non-chemical, non-oral
forms of contraceptives

00:12:41.740 --> 00:12:44.645 align:middle line:10%
of pretty much any kind, but
just don't take the pill.

00:12:44.645 --> 00:12:46.770 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah, go back
to the old fashioned ways

00:12:46.770 --> 00:12:52.300 align:middle line:84%
of doing things, condom and
you know just self-control.

00:12:52.300 --> 00:12:53.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:12:53.100 --> 00:12:54.240 align:middle line:84%
And I think with
a lot of people,

00:12:54.240 --> 00:12:56.370 align:middle line:84%
they just don't want the
inconvenience of not knowing,

00:12:56.370 --> 00:12:58.412 align:middle line:84%
for example, when their
period's going to show up

00:12:58.412 --> 00:12:59.910 align:middle line:84%
in the case of
girls, and it just

00:12:59.910 --> 00:13:02.370 align:middle line:84%
seems like an easy conventional
way to do things now.

00:13:02.370 --> 00:13:03.953 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: OK, so
this is what I say,

00:13:03.953 --> 00:13:08.490 align:middle line:84%
because this is what I hear,
the cramps, and the mood swings,

00:13:08.490 --> 00:13:10.170 align:middle line:90%
and the inconvenience.

00:13:10.170 --> 00:13:12.540 align:middle line:90%
Well, so what?

00:13:12.540 --> 00:13:13.770 align:middle line:90%
You're a girl.

00:13:13.770 --> 00:13:15.210 align:middle line:90%
You're a woman.

00:13:15.210 --> 00:13:16.190 align:middle line:90%
Deal with.

00:13:16.190 --> 00:13:19.920 align:middle line:84%
However, the reason we
have symptoms like that

00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:22.170 align:middle line:84%
is because we have
hormone imbalance.

00:13:22.170 --> 00:13:24.680 align:middle line:84%
So we can get the
hormones in balance.

00:13:24.680 --> 00:13:27.420 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people, once
their hormones are in balance,

00:13:27.420 --> 00:13:29.640 align:middle line:90%
they don't have symptoms.

00:13:29.640 --> 00:13:32.970 align:middle line:84%
They go through the period
without pretty much blinking

00:13:32.970 --> 00:13:34.300 align:middle line:90%
an eye.

00:13:34.300 --> 00:13:35.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so
give us an example.

00:13:35.800 --> 00:13:39.090 align:middle line:84%
So you have a girl who
is suffering from cramps

00:13:39.090 --> 00:13:41.850 align:middle line:84%
and all these things you just
mentioned that are painful,

00:13:41.850 --> 00:13:44.460 align:middle line:84%
unpleasant, just make life
miserable for a couple of days,

00:13:44.460 --> 00:13:46.680 align:middle line:84%
what would you do to
that girl to balance

00:13:46.680 --> 00:13:49.710 align:middle line:84%
her hormones without
her taking anything

00:13:49.710 --> 00:13:51.123 align:middle line:90%
like an oral contraceptive?

00:13:51.123 --> 00:13:52.290 align:middle line:90%
What would your approach be?

00:13:52.290 --> 00:13:54.165 align:middle line:10%
>>THOMPSON: I always go
back to the baseline,

00:13:54.165 --> 00:13:55.300 align:middle line:10%
which is your food.

00:13:55.300 --> 00:13:57.810 align:middle line:84%
OK, what the information
you can give someone

00:13:57.810 --> 00:14:00.060 align:middle line:84%
about the food,
and the information

00:14:00.060 --> 00:14:03.000 align:middle line:84%
that they glean from their
body from eating certain foods

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:06.460 align:middle line:84%
or not, it's going
to last a lifetime.

00:14:06.460 --> 00:14:09.660 align:middle line:84%
And so, what I talk about
is, pretty much largely

00:14:09.660 --> 00:14:10.645 align:middle line:90%
blood sugar.

00:14:10.645 --> 00:14:12.270 align:middle line:84%
How to keep the blood
sugar in balance,

00:14:12.270 --> 00:14:14.228 align:middle line:84%
because when the blood
sugar is out of balance,

00:14:14.228 --> 00:14:16.710 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of people
are hypoglycemic, which

00:14:16.710 --> 00:14:19.500 align:middle line:84%
means the blood
sugar gets low, well,

00:14:19.500 --> 00:14:22.770 align:middle line:84%
that sets up off a
whole cascade of events,

00:14:22.770 --> 00:14:28.350 align:middle line:84%
not the least of which is
mood swings, bitchiness.

00:14:28.350 --> 00:14:30.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, and that
is not-- that does not

00:14:30.780 --> 00:14:31.980 align:middle line:90%
relate just to women.

00:14:31.980 --> 00:14:33.010 align:middle line:90%
That's men as well.

00:14:33.010 --> 00:14:33.450 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Of course.

00:14:33.450 --> 00:14:35.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I had a camera man,
one of my favorite cameramen

00:14:35.790 --> 00:14:37.790 align:middle line:84%
ever, we're out in the
field doing a documentary

00:14:37.790 --> 00:14:41.230 align:middle line:84%
and, oh boy, come three or
4 o'clock in the afternoon,

00:14:41.230 --> 00:14:44.520 align:middle line:84%
everyone knew we needed to
turn the lights on and scream

00:14:44.520 --> 00:14:48.060 align:middle line:84%
through the mountains to find a
coffee shop and something sweet

00:14:48.060 --> 00:14:51.280 align:middle line:84%
because he was so awful to
contend with after that.

00:14:51.280 --> 00:14:55.540 align:middle line:84%
Worst than any woman I knew
on PMS that had PMS going.

00:14:55.540 --> 00:14:58.440 align:middle line:84%
And so, this, do you do the
same-- would it be the same--

00:14:58.440 --> 00:15:00.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, obviously, the same
recommendation for men, women,

00:15:00.940 --> 00:15:01.260 align:middle line:90%
children.

00:15:01.260 --> 00:15:03.410 align:middle line:84%
This is just straight across
advice, balancing blood sugar.

00:15:03.410 --> 00:15:04.620 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: You have
to have a human body.

00:15:04.620 --> 00:15:05.510 align:middle line:90%
This is what you do.

00:15:05.510 --> 00:15:06.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, right.

00:15:06.570 --> 00:15:08.653 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: It's just that
I think with the women,

00:15:08.653 --> 00:15:11.087 align:middle line:90%
things seem more dramatic.

00:15:11.087 --> 00:15:13.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Is it because
women are more expressive?

00:15:13.170 --> 00:15:14.040 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: And more dramatic.

00:15:14.040 --> 00:15:15.390 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And more
dramatic, exactly.

00:15:15.390 --> 00:15:16.848 align:middle line:84%
I mean, just chatting
about it more

00:15:16.848 --> 00:15:18.690 align:middle line:84%
where a guy may be
feeling miserable too,

00:15:18.690 --> 00:15:20.565 align:middle line:84%
but he's not necessarily
going to bring it up

00:15:20.565 --> 00:15:21.420 align:middle line:90%
at breakfast, right?

00:15:21.420 --> 00:15:23.040 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah, And
I think women also--

00:15:23.040 --> 00:15:24.570 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the truth
of the matter is,

00:15:24.570 --> 00:15:27.120 align:middle line:84%
there are cycles that
women go through.

00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:30.360 align:middle line:84%
And men go through cycles too,
but they're a lot more subtle.

00:15:30.360 --> 00:15:34.950 align:middle line:84%
And so anyway, getting
the food in order

00:15:34.950 --> 00:15:41.650 align:middle line:84%
and helping a young girl
eat five small meals a day--

00:15:41.650 --> 00:15:43.230 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of times,
their schedules

00:15:43.230 --> 00:15:45.870 align:middle line:84%
are conducive to that,
especially if they're athletes.

00:15:45.870 --> 00:15:49.980 align:middle line:84%
And they just take
little snacks with them.

00:15:49.980 --> 00:15:54.730 align:middle line:84%
And then it's really a question
of doing the hormone testing.

00:15:54.730 --> 00:15:55.530 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:15:55.530 --> 00:15:57.940 align:middle line:10%
And we're going to get
to that in just a minute.

00:15:57.940 --> 00:16:00.900 align:middle line:10%
But what often happens
for people in their teens,

00:16:00.900 --> 00:16:03.480 align:middle line:10%
and once you have some wheels
and a little bit of freedom,

00:16:03.480 --> 00:16:06.120 align:middle line:10%
is you head to a place
like Starbucks, right?

00:16:06.120 --> 00:16:08.410 align:middle line:84%
And so you would take
that afternoon snack

00:16:08.410 --> 00:16:11.670 align:middle line:84%
and turn it into maybe a
triple venti vanilla latte.

00:16:11.670 --> 00:16:13.540 align:middle line:84%
And now you've got
caffeine in on it.

00:16:13.540 --> 00:16:16.170 align:middle line:10%
You have simple refined
sugars in on it.

00:16:16.170 --> 00:16:19.890 align:middle line:84%
What is that further doing to a
girl or a woman at this point?

00:16:19.890 --> 00:16:21.900 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah,
you're creating a yo-yo.

00:16:21.900 --> 00:16:24.360 align:middle line:84%
And you're basically
stepping in for the adrenals.

00:16:24.360 --> 00:16:27.300 align:middle line:84%
Anything that's a stimulant
like sugar or caffeine

00:16:27.300 --> 00:16:30.490 align:middle line:84%
is going to step in
and say, hey, I'm here.

00:16:30.490 --> 00:16:31.680 align:middle line:90%
I'm the stimulant.

00:16:31.680 --> 00:16:33.990 align:middle line:84%
We don't need new
adrenals right now.

00:16:33.990 --> 00:16:35.880 align:middle line:84%
And basically, the
body eventually

00:16:35.880 --> 00:16:39.780 align:middle line:84%
starts to rely on that, because
the body's own resources for it

00:16:39.780 --> 00:16:42.000 align:middle line:90%
have been cast aside.

00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:47.700 align:middle line:84%
And thus, the cravings
ensue, and the habits form.

00:16:47.700 --> 00:16:50.637 align:middle line:10%
But, you know, not to say
that all of these things

00:16:50.637 --> 00:16:52.470 align:middle line:10%
need to be eliminated
100%, because you know

00:16:52.470 --> 00:16:53.350 align:middle line:10%
that's not going to happen.

00:16:53.350 --> 00:16:54.030 align:middle line:90%
We're human beings.

00:16:54.030 --> 00:16:54.720 align:middle line:90%
We're created--

00:16:54.720 --> 00:16:56.553 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We just can't
live that lifestyle.

00:16:56.553 --> 00:16:57.720 align:middle line:90%
We can't do it as a daily--

00:16:57.720 --> 00:16:59.358 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Lifestyle
is a good word.

00:16:59.358 --> 00:17:00.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: As a lifestyle.

00:17:00.400 --> 00:17:02.370 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about-- you were
just talking about cravings.

00:17:02.370 --> 00:17:03.480 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about sex.

00:17:03.480 --> 00:17:05.910 align:middle line:84%
What happens with people
once you start really

00:17:05.910 --> 00:17:08.520 align:middle line:84%
spending the adrenals
and you start going out

00:17:08.520 --> 00:17:10.342 align:middle line:90%
of balance hormonally?

00:17:10.342 --> 00:17:12.300 align:middle line:84%
We look at the birth rate
of various countries,

00:17:12.300 --> 00:17:13.925 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of it has
to do with choices,

00:17:13.925 --> 00:17:17.680 align:middle line:84%
birth control, finances,
economics, and so forth.

00:17:17.680 --> 00:17:22.740 align:middle line:10%
But what's actually happening
to the modern person

00:17:22.740 --> 00:17:25.589 align:middle line:10%
as a result of these
stressors and their sex drive?

00:17:25.589 --> 00:17:28.349 align:middle line:10%
You see a lot of people
coming through your office.

00:17:28.349 --> 00:17:29.492 align:middle line:10%
What's happening to us?

00:17:29.492 --> 00:17:31.700 align:middle line:10%
>>THOMPSON: Well, I see it
going both ways, you know?

00:17:31.700 --> 00:17:34.350 align:middle line:10%
I see the low, and
I see the high.

00:17:34.350 --> 00:17:38.890 align:middle line:10%
And I'm talking about the low
for men too, not just women.

00:17:38.890 --> 00:17:42.600 align:middle line:10%
But I also work with people
who have sexual addictions.

00:17:42.600 --> 00:17:47.460 align:middle line:84%
And this is where we really
see the adrenal and the brain

00:17:47.460 --> 00:17:50.310 align:middle line:84%
connection, the
neurotransmitters of the brain,

00:17:50.310 --> 00:17:52.440 align:middle line:84%
the brain chemicals
that interact

00:17:52.440 --> 00:17:56.520 align:middle line:84%
with the adrenal glands and are
affected by various stressors

00:17:56.520 --> 00:17:57.870 align:middle line:90%
that we mentioned before.

00:17:57.870 --> 00:17:59.730 align:middle line:84%
And again, a whole
cascade of events

00:17:59.730 --> 00:18:02.790 align:middle line:90%
occurs with the brain chemicals.

00:18:02.790 --> 00:18:04.980 align:middle line:10%
But when the adrenal
glands are depleted,

00:18:04.980 --> 00:18:09.090 align:middle line:10%
what that means is that the
body then cannot accurately,

00:18:09.090 --> 00:18:11.910 align:middle line:10%
effectively deal with stressors.

00:18:11.910 --> 00:18:15.510 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, the brain is
triggered in certain ways

00:18:15.510 --> 00:18:18.690 align:middle line:84%
to help sort of
balance things out.

00:18:18.690 --> 00:18:24.000 align:middle line:84%
And then the neurotransmitters
can either be deficient

00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:27.510 align:middle line:84%
or can be excreted
in high amounts.

00:18:27.510 --> 00:18:30.540 align:middle line:84%
And one of them--
dopamine, for instance--

00:18:30.540 --> 00:18:34.080 align:middle line:84%
is known when it's low to
actually cause a person

00:18:34.080 --> 00:18:37.320 align:middle line:90%
to want to feel stimulated.

00:18:37.320 --> 00:18:39.810 align:middle line:84%
In other words,
caffeine can give you

00:18:39.810 --> 00:18:42.540 align:middle line:84%
that jolt that if you
don't have dopamine,

00:18:42.540 --> 00:18:45.810 align:middle line:84%
you'll feel some sort of
satisfaction or motivation.

00:18:45.810 --> 00:18:47.268 align:middle line:84%
The same with--
this is what I find

00:18:47.268 --> 00:18:49.352 align:middle line:84%
with people with sex
addictions is a lot of times,

00:18:49.352 --> 00:18:50.655 align:middle line:90%
their dopamine levels are low.

00:18:50.655 --> 00:18:51.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, I see.

00:18:51.210 --> 00:18:51.480 align:middle line:90%
Interesting.

00:18:51.480 --> 00:18:53.022 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: And
therefore, the body's

00:18:53.022 --> 00:18:56.100 align:middle line:84%
going to try and do something
to get it to go up so that it

00:18:56.100 --> 00:18:58.560 align:middle line:90%
gets that sense of motivation.

00:18:58.560 --> 00:18:59.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:18:59.360 --> 00:19:03.970 align:middle line:10%
And what about in the case where
your sexual desire is very low,

00:19:03.970 --> 00:19:05.580 align:middle line:10%
which you hear that a lot?

00:19:05.580 --> 00:19:06.510 align:middle line:90%
A lot that is age--

00:19:06.510 --> 00:19:08.560 align:middle line:84%
seems to be age-related
as well, of course.

00:19:08.560 --> 00:19:10.380 align:middle line:84%
But what about en
masse, I mean, even

00:19:10.380 --> 00:19:15.390 align:middle line:84%
among young people who normally
are kind of in those more

00:19:15.390 --> 00:19:17.460 align:middle line:84%
juicy years of
childbearing and such,

00:19:17.460 --> 00:19:19.022 align:middle line:90%
but there's just no desire?

00:19:19.022 --> 00:19:19.980 align:middle line:90%
What's happening there?

00:19:19.980 --> 00:19:20.940 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: I had
a 16-year-old boy

00:19:20.940 --> 00:19:22.530 align:middle line:84%
in my office a
couple of weeks ago

00:19:22.530 --> 00:19:24.510 align:middle line:90%
saying that his libido is low.

00:19:24.510 --> 00:19:27.090 align:middle line:84%
He asked his mom to
go out of the room,

00:19:27.090 --> 00:19:29.670 align:middle line:90%
and says that his libido is low.

00:19:29.670 --> 00:19:31.660 align:middle line:84%
And I said, what
do you need it for?

00:19:31.660 --> 00:19:32.705 align:middle line:90%
No, I'm just kidding.

00:19:32.705 --> 00:19:33.505 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I know.

00:19:33.505 --> 00:19:34.808 align:middle line:90%
Come on.

00:19:34.808 --> 00:19:36.600 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: No, he knew
his libido was low.

00:19:36.600 --> 00:19:39.910 align:middle line:84%
He didn't have that
thing that guys have.

00:19:39.910 --> 00:19:43.470 align:middle line:84%
And so I said,
well, it's probably

00:19:43.470 --> 00:19:45.480 align:middle line:90%
because your hormones are low.

00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:47.380 align:middle line:84%
So what we're
looking at here are

00:19:47.380 --> 00:19:49.830 align:middle line:84%
a variety of, in
the case of a guy,

00:19:49.830 --> 00:19:52.260 align:middle line:90%
potential low testosterone.

00:19:52.260 --> 00:19:54.750 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that we
look at with boys and men

00:19:54.750 --> 00:19:58.680 align:middle line:84%
is the ratio between
testosterone and estrogens,

00:19:58.680 --> 00:20:01.500 align:middle line:84%
because nowadays with all
the estrogens in the dairy

00:20:01.500 --> 00:20:03.070 align:middle line:90%
products and the environment--

00:20:03.070 --> 00:20:03.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's what
I was going to ask you.

00:20:03.570 --> 00:20:05.790 align:middle line:10%
What if your household
is vegetarian,

00:20:05.790 --> 00:20:08.390 align:middle line:10%
and you're living on
also maybe a lot of soy

00:20:08.390 --> 00:20:10.290 align:middle line:10%
that has a high
estrogen content?

00:20:10.290 --> 00:20:11.785 align:middle line:90%
What is that doing to the males?

00:20:11.785 --> 00:20:14.160 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah, so it's
taking up the estrogen receptor

00:20:14.160 --> 00:20:15.250 align:middle line:90%
sites in the body.

00:20:15.250 --> 00:20:19.040 align:middle line:84%
It can be causing some
liver ineffectiveness.

00:20:19.040 --> 00:20:22.710 align:middle line:84%
And the liver is very important
for the production of hormones.

00:20:22.710 --> 00:20:25.910 align:middle line:84%
The word that's used is
conjugation of hormones.

00:20:25.910 --> 00:20:29.680 align:middle line:84%
And so all of these foods
and environmental factors

00:20:29.680 --> 00:20:32.350 align:middle line:90%
are upsetting the apple cart.

00:20:32.350 --> 00:20:34.900 align:middle line:84%
And what we have to do is
we have to analyze the diet,

00:20:34.900 --> 00:20:40.300 align:middle line:84%
see what needs to come out, and
help the liver and the gut work

00:20:40.300 --> 00:20:44.800 align:middle line:84%
more effectively, and then do
the normal hormone balancing

00:20:44.800 --> 00:20:46.727 align:middle line:90%
that we do.

00:20:46.727 --> 00:20:48.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's
interesting because you

00:20:48.310 --> 00:20:50.350 align:middle line:84%
look at a lot of
third-world cultures

00:20:50.350 --> 00:20:54.080 align:middle line:84%
where you have birth rates of
up to seven to nine children,

00:20:54.080 --> 00:20:54.880 align:middle line:90%
even.

00:20:54.880 --> 00:20:57.310 align:middle line:84%
But then again, you're looking
at people who oftentimes

00:20:57.310 --> 00:20:59.140 align:middle line:90%
live very close to the land.

00:20:59.140 --> 00:21:01.300 align:middle line:84%
They're not interfacing
with a lot of technology

00:21:01.300 --> 00:21:03.160 align:middle line:90%
if any technology at all.

00:21:03.160 --> 00:21:05.710 align:middle line:84%
They're eating diets that
are much closer to the land

00:21:05.710 --> 00:21:07.062 align:middle line:90%
and not processed.

00:21:07.062 --> 00:21:08.770 align:middle line:84%
Basically, what I'm
saying is these women

00:21:08.770 --> 00:21:11.890 align:middle line:84%
tend to be a lot closer
to nature in every way

00:21:11.890 --> 00:21:12.850 align:middle line:90%
than we are.

00:21:12.850 --> 00:21:14.650 align:middle line:10%
Is this what you
think is responsible

00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:19.390 align:middle line:10%
for these further high
fertility rates compared to us?

00:21:19.390 --> 00:21:21.050 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: I think
that's part of it.

00:21:21.050 --> 00:21:25.750 align:middle line:84%
And I think also, the way
that women live today with

00:21:25.750 --> 00:21:30.250 align:middle line:84%
their very high testosterone
output because they're doing

00:21:30.250 --> 00:21:33.370 align:middle line:84%
a lot of work, and they're
trying to maintain households,

00:21:33.370 --> 00:21:38.110 align:middle line:84%
and they're doing man-woman
jobs at the same time--

00:21:38.110 --> 00:21:41.170 align:middle line:84%
I think that's affecting the
balance of the sex hormones,

00:21:41.170 --> 00:21:43.570 align:middle line:84%
and it's also affecting
the adrenal glands, which,

00:21:43.570 --> 00:21:46.060 align:middle line:84%
as I said before, are
not then available to be

00:21:46.060 --> 00:21:47.500 align:middle line:90%
the backup system.

00:21:47.500 --> 00:21:48.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, exactly.

00:21:48.910 --> 00:21:49.710 align:middle line:90%
OK.

