00:21:58.960 --> 00:22:02.110 align:middle line:10%
talking about our digestive
function and how all of that

00:22:02.110 --> 00:22:05.160 align:middle line:10%
plays into it, particularly
with serotonin.

00:22:05.160 --> 00:22:06.910 align:middle line:10%
And we haven't talked
about serotonin yet,

00:22:06.910 --> 00:22:08.770 align:middle line:10%
but that's that nice,
soft, feel-good thing.

00:22:08.770 --> 00:22:11.470 align:middle line:10%
That's why when we're
upset, we go and eat a donut

00:22:11.470 --> 00:22:13.420 align:middle line:10%
and want a cup of
hot chocolate--

00:22:13.420 --> 00:22:16.720 align:middle line:10%
all because our brain is craving
some production of serotonin

00:22:16.720 --> 00:22:18.700 align:middle line:10%
to make us feel better.

00:22:18.700 --> 00:22:21.275 align:middle line:10%
How does this play into
the hormonal portrait?

00:22:21.275 --> 00:22:22.900 align:middle line:10%
Because we don't seem
to be running off

00:22:22.900 --> 00:22:24.970 align:middle line:10%
of serotonin as a lot.

00:22:24.970 --> 00:22:25.770 align:middle line:10%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah.

00:22:25.770 --> 00:22:30.340 align:middle line:10%
So when we have stress,
it depletes serotonin,

00:22:30.340 --> 00:22:35.560 align:middle line:10%
and it affects so many
events in the body that can

00:22:35.560 --> 00:22:38.650 align:middle line:10%
cause a decrease in serotonin.

00:22:38.650 --> 00:22:42.040 align:middle line:84%
But the whole thing
with the dietary issues

00:22:42.040 --> 00:22:44.680 align:middle line:84%
and all of the
inflammatory problems

00:22:44.680 --> 00:22:47.530 align:middle line:84%
that occur in the gut
between the gluten

00:22:47.530 --> 00:22:49.630 align:middle line:84%
and the wheat and the
casein and the dairy

00:22:49.630 --> 00:22:55.480 align:middle line:84%
products and the sugar and the
alcohol and the inflammation

00:22:55.480 --> 00:23:01.750 align:middle line:84%
that the body incurs is one
of the destroying factors

00:23:01.750 --> 00:23:03.290 align:middle line:90%
of serotonin.

00:23:03.290 --> 00:23:06.670 align:middle line:84%
So there is a huge dietary
influence on whether or not

00:23:06.670 --> 00:23:07.690 align:middle line:90%
serotonin is produced.

00:23:07.690 --> 00:23:10.690 align:middle line:84%
90% to 95% of
serotonin is produced

00:23:10.690 --> 00:23:13.428 align:middle line:84%
in the enteric nervous
system, in the gut

00:23:13.428 --> 00:23:14.470 align:middle line:90%
and the intestinal tract.

00:23:14.470 --> 00:23:15.803 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So what does that say?

00:23:15.803 --> 00:23:18.310 align:middle line:84%
Say now, you've eaten
so much of that stuff.

00:23:18.310 --> 00:23:20.020 align:middle line:10%
We're allergic to
a lot of things,

00:23:20.020 --> 00:23:22.210 align:middle line:10%
like you just said, a
lot of food allergies.

00:23:22.210 --> 00:23:24.730 align:middle line:10%
If we were originally
eating grains in order

00:23:24.730 --> 00:23:27.310 align:middle line:10%
to help in the
production of serotonin,

00:23:27.310 --> 00:23:31.030 align:middle line:10%
what happens now with people who
can't even eat grains anymore

00:23:31.030 --> 00:23:32.980 align:middle line:10%
and can't eat a lot
of the foods that

00:23:32.980 --> 00:23:34.870 align:middle line:10%
normally would have
easily inspired

00:23:34.870 --> 00:23:36.910 align:middle line:10%
the production of serotonin?

00:23:36.910 --> 00:23:38.650 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Well, it
comes down to how--

00:23:38.650 --> 00:23:41.210 align:middle line:84%
serotonin is made
from amino acids.

00:23:41.210 --> 00:23:42.820 align:middle line:90%
Amino acids are from protein.

00:23:42.820 --> 00:23:44.830 align:middle line:84%
So it really comes down
to how is your body

00:23:44.830 --> 00:23:48.293 align:middle line:84%
actually digesting and absorbing
the protein that you're eating.

00:23:48.293 --> 00:23:49.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:23:49.210 --> 00:23:51.610 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: And what kind
of proteins are you eating?

00:23:51.610 --> 00:23:55.280 align:middle line:84%
Are they able to then
become serotonin?

00:23:55.280 --> 00:23:58.030 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, I mean, it
doesn't necessarily

00:23:58.030 --> 00:23:59.260 align:middle line:90%
have to do with the carbs.

00:23:59.260 --> 00:24:00.940 align:middle line:90%
I mean, the carbohydrate--

00:24:00.940 --> 00:24:03.167 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Why do we grab--
why do we reach for carbs?

00:24:03.167 --> 00:24:04.750 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Well,
it's-- yeah, I mean,

00:24:04.750 --> 00:24:07.240 align:middle line:84%
it's sort of our intuitive
nature of what's going to get

00:24:07.240 --> 00:24:10.370 align:middle line:84%
me there the quickest, which is
not necessarily always the best

00:24:10.370 --> 00:24:11.170 align:middle line:90%
way.

00:24:11.170 --> 00:24:11.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:24:11.980 --> 00:24:15.040 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: But
the carb situation

00:24:15.040 --> 00:24:19.060 align:middle line:84%
is such that if you eat
complex carbohydrates, which

00:24:19.060 --> 00:24:22.870 align:middle line:84%
are the better ones, the brown
rice and that type of thing,

00:24:22.870 --> 00:24:26.680 align:middle line:84%
then the body is going to
utilize the carbohydrates

00:24:26.680 --> 00:24:30.970 align:middle line:84%
and break down in
a slower manner

00:24:30.970 --> 00:24:33.760 align:middle line:84%
so that the body
gets more even fuel.

00:24:33.760 --> 00:24:35.710 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't necessarily
say that one

00:24:35.710 --> 00:24:38.230 align:middle line:84%
should bank on carbohydrates
to produce serotonin

00:24:38.230 --> 00:24:41.100 align:middle line:84%
because if you do, you're
basically looking at a roller

00:24:41.100 --> 00:24:46.387 align:middle line:84%
coaster effect, which could be
fun in a short period of time.

00:24:46.387 --> 00:24:48.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, if you want to
go manic and then be depressed.

00:24:48.970 --> 00:24:50.270 align:middle line:90%
Great for manic depression.

00:24:50.270 --> 00:24:51.070 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah.

00:24:51.070 --> 00:24:53.050 align:middle line:84%
But basically, that's
not really a way

00:24:53.050 --> 00:24:54.260 align:middle line:90%
to have consistent happiness.

00:24:54.260 --> 00:24:55.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:24:55.060 --> 00:24:57.280 align:middle line:10%
So you're saying really,
it's down to the quality,

00:24:57.280 --> 00:24:59.510 align:middle line:10%
regardless of our
dietary restrictions,

00:24:59.510 --> 00:25:03.520 align:middle line:10%
whether we're a raw foodist, a
vegan, a vegetarian, a lacto,

00:25:03.520 --> 00:25:08.260 align:middle line:10%
ovo, whatever, or paleo,
on a paleo diet of mostly

00:25:08.260 --> 00:25:09.650 align:middle line:10%
vegetables and proteins.

00:25:09.650 --> 00:25:12.700 align:middle line:10%
We have to find a
consistent source of protein

00:25:12.700 --> 00:25:14.380 align:middle line:10%
that works well for our bodies.

00:25:14.380 --> 00:25:16.330 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Exactly, right.

00:25:16.330 --> 00:25:18.900 align:middle line:84%
It's those proteins
that actually break down

00:25:18.900 --> 00:25:20.880 align:middle line:90%
to the various amino acids.

00:25:20.880 --> 00:25:23.970 align:middle line:84%
You know, I have this
discussion with--

00:25:23.970 --> 00:25:26.910 align:middle line:84%
I see a lot of people who
are on antidepressant meds.

00:25:26.910 --> 00:25:29.540 align:middle line:84%
And I see a lot of people
who are on anti-anxiety meds

00:25:29.540 --> 00:25:32.310 align:middle line:90%
and sleep medications.

00:25:32.310 --> 00:25:35.250 align:middle line:84%
And so most of time,
they're coming to me

00:25:35.250 --> 00:25:36.870 align:middle line:84%
because they want
to get off of them.

00:25:36.870 --> 00:25:39.510 align:middle line:84%
And I say, OK, I can't take
you off your medication.

00:25:39.510 --> 00:25:41.380 align:middle line:90%
That's not my role.

00:25:41.380 --> 00:25:44.490 align:middle line:84%
My role is to help your
body get to the point

00:25:44.490 --> 00:25:46.890 align:middle line:84%
where you don't
need them anymore.

00:25:46.890 --> 00:25:50.160 align:middle line:84%
But a lot of people
are brainwashed

00:25:50.160 --> 00:25:51.720 align:middle line:84%
into thinking that
they can never

00:25:51.720 --> 00:25:53.325 align:middle line:84%
get off their
medications because this

00:25:53.325 --> 00:25:54.818 align:middle line:90%
is what they're told.

00:25:54.818 --> 00:25:57.360 align:middle line:84%
And they're told this because
the people who are telling them

00:25:57.360 --> 00:26:00.090 align:middle line:84%
this, they're
psychiatrists, and whoever

00:26:00.090 --> 00:26:01.253 align:middle line:90%
is prescribing for them--

00:26:01.253 --> 00:26:02.670 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Someone
in a white coat.

00:26:02.670 --> 00:26:04.020 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: They don't know.

00:26:04.020 --> 00:26:06.750 align:middle line:84%
They don't know that the
brain chemicals are only

00:26:06.750 --> 00:26:08.370 align:middle line:90%
made from nutrients.

00:26:08.370 --> 00:26:10.410 align:middle line:84%
The brain chemicals
are made from minerals

00:26:10.410 --> 00:26:15.150 align:middle line:84%
and amino acids and vitamin
C. And these nutrients,

00:26:15.150 --> 00:26:19.650 align:middle line:84%
they follow a particular cascade
with certain enzyme reactions

00:26:19.650 --> 00:26:21.900 align:middle line:84%
in the body and liver
function that all

00:26:21.900 --> 00:26:23.910 align:middle line:90%
make the right thing happen.

00:26:23.910 --> 00:26:28.110 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, the pathway
of minerals and nutrients

00:26:28.110 --> 00:26:31.360 align:middle line:84%
and amino acids becomes
the final product,

00:26:31.360 --> 00:26:32.890 align:middle line:90%
which is the neurotransmitter.

00:26:32.890 --> 00:26:35.790 align:middle line:84%
So if a person is getting
nourished properly

00:26:35.790 --> 00:26:39.730 align:middle line:84%
and the gut is set up to be able
to absorb your food properly,

00:26:39.730 --> 00:26:42.540 align:middle line:84%
then the potential is
that you can actually

00:26:42.540 --> 00:26:44.470 align:middle line:84%
manufacture these
chemicals on your own,

00:26:44.470 --> 00:26:45.720 align:middle line:90%
which is the way it should be.

00:26:45.720 --> 00:26:47.240 align:middle line:90%
This is how we were designed.

00:26:47.240 --> 00:26:48.740 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So what
if the food source

00:26:48.740 --> 00:26:50.790 align:middle line:84%
is denuded of any
natural minerals?

00:26:50.790 --> 00:26:53.610 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we know
that even if you're

00:26:53.610 --> 00:26:55.740 align:middle line:84%
talking about fresh
produce, unless it's

00:26:55.740 --> 00:26:57.300 align:middle line:84%
raised in a very
conscious way, which

00:26:57.300 --> 00:27:00.090 align:middle line:84%
used to be just the normal
way, a lot of the minerals

00:27:00.090 --> 00:27:01.720 align:middle line:90%
are now missing from the diet.

00:27:01.720 --> 00:27:04.990 align:middle line:84%
So how do we start
replenishing the minerals,

00:27:04.990 --> 00:27:06.390 align:middle line:90%
remineralize our body?

00:27:06.390 --> 00:27:08.760 align:middle line:84%
Do you have some
suggestions for us, even

00:27:08.760 --> 00:27:11.160 align:middle line:84%
by way of supplementation
of reliable minerals

00:27:11.160 --> 00:27:13.650 align:middle line:84%
to start kicking
this process back

00:27:13.650 --> 00:27:16.690 align:middle line:84%
in so we can create our own
proper hormone spectrum?

00:27:16.690 --> 00:27:19.080 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Well, first
of all, as you mentioned,

00:27:19.080 --> 00:27:24.180 align:middle line:84%
using organic produce,
vegetables, and fruits,

00:27:24.180 --> 00:27:28.128 align:middle line:84%
you're going to be getting a
highly mineralized soil, which

00:27:28.128 --> 00:27:30.420 align:middle line:84%
is going to pass it on to
the plant, and then the food,

00:27:30.420 --> 00:27:32.070 align:middle line:90%
and then into your body.

00:27:32.070 --> 00:27:35.730 align:middle line:84%
So I mean, many studies have
looked at organic produce

00:27:35.730 --> 00:27:40.410 align:middle line:84%
and shown that they are
much higher in nutrients.

00:27:40.410 --> 00:27:41.940 align:middle line:90%
So that's one.

00:27:41.940 --> 00:27:45.270 align:middle line:84%
I utilize lots of different
products in my practice.

00:27:45.270 --> 00:27:50.370 align:middle line:84%
I love the old coral
calcium minerals.

00:27:50.370 --> 00:27:54.690 align:middle line:84%
They are so pH balanced, and
the body just takes them up,

00:27:54.690 --> 00:27:58.192 align:middle line:90%
just sort of takes it right in.

00:27:58.192 --> 00:28:00.150 align:middle line:84%
That happens to be one
