for infections.

00:31:18.407 --> 00:31:20.115 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
malabsorption of nutrients?

00:31:20.115 --> 00:31:21.032 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Of course.

00:31:21.032 --> 00:31:24.170 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you never want to
take laxatives and expect

00:31:24.170 --> 00:31:26.720 align:middle line:84%
that you're not going to
have mineral or vitamin

00:31:26.720 --> 00:31:27.980 align:middle line:90%
malabsorption.

00:31:27.980 --> 00:31:30.313 align:middle line:84%
You always want to
take extra nutrients

00:31:30.313 --> 00:31:31.730 align:middle line:84%
when you're taking
that laxatives,

00:31:31.730 --> 00:31:32.893 align:middle line:90%
because they're going to--

00:31:32.893 --> 00:31:34.810 align:middle line:84%
they're just going to
help your body eliminate

00:31:34.810 --> 00:31:35.790 align:middle line:90%
indiscriminately.

00:31:35.790 --> 00:31:36.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:31:36.590 --> 00:31:39.950 align:middle line:84%
So does that feed
into leaky gut at all?

00:31:39.950 --> 00:31:42.650 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Well, does
it feed into leaky gut?

00:31:42.650 --> 00:31:44.925 align:middle line:90%
Well, I mean, it could.

00:31:44.925 --> 00:31:46.300 align:middle line:84%
It could, but it
doesn't have to.

00:31:46.300 --> 00:31:47.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'm saying if you've
got all this stuff sticking

00:31:47.900 --> 00:31:50.150 align:middle line:84%
around the lining of the
intestines, for example.

00:31:50.150 --> 00:31:53.068 align:middle line:84%
I mean, are you setting yourself
up for something chronic?

00:31:53.068 --> 00:31:54.110 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: You could be.

00:31:54.110 --> 00:31:54.950 align:middle line:90%
You could be, yeah.

00:31:54.950 --> 00:31:58.000 align:middle line:84%
Because eventually,
over time, the way I

00:31:58.000 --> 00:32:02.540 align:middle line:84%
usually explain it if
something is irritating--

00:32:02.540 --> 00:32:05.030 align:middle line:84%
or say you're rubbing your
finger on a piece of paper day

00:32:05.030 --> 00:32:07.633 align:middle line:84%
after day, week after
week, month after month.

00:32:07.633 --> 00:32:09.800 align:middle line:84%
Eventually, you're going
to rub a hole in the paper.

00:32:09.800 --> 00:32:11.450 align:middle line:84%
And for things
that are irritating

00:32:11.450 --> 00:32:14.540 align:middle line:84%
the intestinal lining, which
could be anything from gluten

00:32:14.540 --> 00:32:21.032 align:middle line:84%
to infections, staph,
parasites, yeast, eventually,

00:32:21.032 --> 00:32:22.490 align:middle line:84%
what's going to
happen is there are

00:32:22.490 --> 00:32:25.280 align:middle line:84%
going to be little tears
in the intestinal tract,

00:32:25.280 --> 00:32:28.100 align:middle line:84%
and then stuff is going to
leak into the bloodstream

00:32:28.100 --> 00:32:29.510 align:middle line:90%
before it's supposed to--

00:32:29.510 --> 00:32:31.170 align:middle line:90%
protein, molecules, et cetera.

00:32:31.170 --> 00:32:32.630 align:middle line:90%
And then the body will attack.

00:32:32.630 --> 00:32:34.995 align:middle line:84%
This is really why we have a
lot of autoimmune problems.

00:32:34.995 --> 00:32:35.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Autoimmune.

00:32:35.870 --> 00:32:37.290 align:middle line:90%
Right, autoimmune.

00:32:37.290 --> 00:32:38.090 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:32:38.090 --> 00:32:42.230 align:middle line:84%
So going back to where we were,
this whole notion of serotonin

00:32:42.230 --> 00:32:44.180 align:middle line:84%
and the production of
the feel-good chemicals

00:32:44.180 --> 00:32:46.123 align:middle line:84%
which allow us to
relax and destress,

00:32:46.123 --> 00:32:47.540 align:middle line:84%
and if we can
destress, then we're

00:32:47.540 --> 00:32:50.630 align:middle line:84%
creating the right cascade,
