>>THOMPSON: I did--
this is on topic,

00:33:36.585 --> 00:33:38.960 align:middle line:84%
but it might start sounding
like it's a little off topic.

00:33:38.960 --> 00:33:39.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Go ahead.

00:33:39.890 --> 00:33:42.350 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: I did a great
experiment with myself

00:33:42.350 --> 00:33:45.560 align:middle line:84%
when I went into menopause
about 12 years ago.

00:33:45.560 --> 00:33:49.040 align:middle line:84%
I had horrendous hot
flashes, 50 to 60 a day,

00:33:49.040 --> 00:33:52.400 align:middle line:84%
I mean, sometimes full body
sweats, horrible-- two,

00:33:52.400 --> 00:33:56.180 align:middle line:84%
three showers a day, waking
up 10 times at night,

00:33:56.180 --> 00:33:59.870 align:middle line:84%
really not even wanting to
go anywhere near the bedroom

00:33:59.870 --> 00:34:04.550 align:middle line:84%
because I started associating
it with horrendous discomfort.

00:34:04.550 --> 00:34:07.970 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, I started to analyze
my hot flashes, because I mean,

00:34:07.970 --> 00:34:09.550 align:middle line:90%
I'm a hormone expert.

00:34:09.550 --> 00:34:13.310 align:middle line:84%
So I can't be sitting
there having hot flashes.

00:34:13.310 --> 00:34:15.530 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, I've worked
on myself, and I

00:34:15.530 --> 00:34:18.350 align:middle line:84%
let other people work on
me, because that's really--

00:34:18.350 --> 00:34:21.469 align:middle line:90%
physician, heal thyself, right?

00:34:21.469 --> 00:34:25.280 align:middle line:84%
And I started analyzing
by thinking back.

00:34:25.280 --> 00:34:27.560 align:middle line:84%
OK, what just happened
10 seconds ago?

00:34:27.560 --> 00:34:29.810 align:middle line:90%
What brought this hot flash on?

00:34:29.810 --> 00:34:31.550 align:middle line:84%
Was it the iced
tea I just drank?

00:34:31.550 --> 00:34:33.949 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:34:33.949 --> 00:34:36.500 align:middle line:90%
Was it what somebody just said?

00:34:36.500 --> 00:34:39.620 align:middle line:84%
And I started analyzing
how my reactions were

00:34:39.620 --> 00:34:41.570 align:middle line:90%
to certain people.

00:34:41.570 --> 00:34:45.469 align:middle line:84%
There would invariably be a
patient or two or a person

00:34:45.469 --> 00:34:48.260 align:middle line:84%
that I knew that would come
and sit down in front of me,

00:34:48.260 --> 00:34:51.770 align:middle line:84%
and my face would
start dripping sweat.

00:34:51.770 --> 00:34:53.870 align:middle line:84%
And I think, what is it
about this person that I'm

00:34:53.870 --> 00:34:57.020 align:middle line:84%
getting stressed out
about, whether it be fear

00:34:57.020 --> 00:34:59.750 align:middle line:84%
or whatever emotion
was coming over me?

00:34:59.750 --> 00:35:03.940 align:middle line:84%
And I started to see that even
joy could create a hot flash.

00:35:03.940 --> 00:35:06.440 align:middle line:10%
A hot flash is basically
the manifestation

00:35:06.440 --> 00:35:10.260 align:middle line:10%
of a stressor, a
stress reaction.

00:35:10.260 --> 00:35:14.800 align:middle line:10%
And so I started seeing
all of these stimulants,

00:35:14.800 --> 00:35:18.510 align:middle line:10%
and I began to realize
that it wasn't just

00:35:18.510 --> 00:35:20.230 align:middle line:10%
a hormone imbalance.

00:35:20.230 --> 00:35:21.890 align:middle line:90%
It was the brain.

00:35:21.890 --> 00:35:23.610 align:middle line:84%
It was what was
happening emotionally,

00:35:23.610 --> 00:35:25.800 align:middle line:84%
what was happening
brain chemical-wise.

00:35:25.800 --> 00:35:27.420 align:middle line:84%
And that's when
I started getting

00:35:27.420 --> 00:35:30.000 align:middle line:90%
into neurotransmitter work.

00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:32.640 align:middle line:84%
And when I began to
work on my serotonin--

00:35:32.640 --> 00:35:35.430 align:middle line:84%
because my serotonin
was in the pits.

00:35:35.430 --> 00:35:38.010 align:middle line:84%
I started working
on serotonin levels.

00:35:38.010 --> 00:35:40.590 align:middle line:84%
And again, I don't like
to think of working

00:35:40.590 --> 00:35:44.070 align:middle line:84%
on anything biochemically
as a single action.

00:35:44.070 --> 00:35:46.120 align:middle line:90%
It's all about a balancing act.

00:35:46.120 --> 00:35:48.270 align:middle line:84%
It's all about the feedback
loop in the body, what

00:35:48.270 --> 00:35:49.470 align:middle line:90%
responds to what.

00:35:49.470 --> 00:35:51.720 align:middle line:84%
It's all about the
ratios of serotonin

00:35:51.720 --> 00:35:54.950 align:middle line:90%
to dopamine, for instance.

00:35:54.950 --> 00:35:57.520 align:middle line:84%
My hot flashes
started disappearing.

00:35:57.520 --> 00:35:59.190 align:middle line:90%
And I was an insomniac.

00:35:59.190 --> 00:36:00.720 align:middle line:90%
My sleep started improving.

00:36:00.720 --> 00:36:01.930 align:middle line:90%
Duh.

00:36:01.930 --> 00:36:06.090 align:middle line:84%
And I really had to
go that extra route

00:36:06.090 --> 00:36:09.600 align:middle line:84%
and go beyond just the
hormone approach to working

00:36:09.600 --> 00:36:10.710 align:middle line:90%
with the brain chemistry.

00:36:10.710 --> 00:36:14.940 align:middle line:84%
Because for me, it was
more about emotions,

00:36:14.940 --> 00:36:15.925 align:middle line:90%
emotional stressors.

00:36:15.925 --> 00:36:17.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That makes sense.

