00:38:05.400 --> 00:38:06.600 align:middle line:84%
It almost seems
chemical, and they're

00:38:06.600 --> 00:38:08.433 align:middle line:84%
having these thoughts
or feelings right now.

00:38:08.433 --> 00:38:11.160 align:middle line:84%
And you want to start
looking at it more seriously

00:38:11.160 --> 00:38:12.100 align:middle line:90%
and evaluating it.

00:38:12.100 --> 00:38:14.232 align:middle line:84%
You have to do some
kind of testing.

00:38:14.232 --> 00:38:15.690 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you go to
your HMO, they'll

00:38:15.690 --> 00:38:17.620 align:middle line:90%
take a vial of blood or two.

00:38:17.620 --> 00:38:18.420 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Or not.

00:38:18.420 --> 00:38:20.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Or not, or not.

00:38:20.360 --> 00:38:22.990 align:middle line:84%
If they take a vial of blood
or two, what's going on there?

00:38:22.990 --> 00:38:24.570 align:middle line:84%
And then talk about,
in your opinion,

00:38:24.570 --> 00:38:27.450 align:middle line:84%
what the preferred
manner of testing is.

00:38:27.450 --> 00:38:29.130 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Ideally,
I like for people

00:38:29.130 --> 00:38:33.300 align:middle line:84%
to do both the saliva
hormone testing as well

00:38:33.300 --> 00:38:35.580 align:middle line:84%
as the urinary
neurotransmitter testing.

00:38:35.580 --> 00:38:36.850 align:middle line:90%
I mean, that would be ideal.

00:38:36.850 --> 00:38:39.183 align:middle line:84%
And the only reason that some
people don't is because it

00:38:39.183 --> 00:38:42.000 align:middle line:90%
gets costly to do everything.

00:38:42.000 --> 00:38:46.530 align:middle line:84%
The salivary testing I find
a lot more impactful to use

00:38:46.530 --> 00:38:49.380 align:middle line:84%
for a treatment
plan than bloodwork,

00:38:49.380 --> 00:38:52.700 align:middle line:84%
mainly because the blood test--
first of all, it's a shot--

00:38:52.700 --> 00:38:54.500 align:middle line:90%
it's a shot in the dark.

00:38:54.500 --> 00:38:55.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Why is--

00:38:55.300 --> 00:38:56.340 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Testing the blood--

00:38:56.340 --> 00:38:58.298 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Is that because
it's just that minute

00:38:58.298 --> 00:38:59.300 align:middle line:90%
versus over 24 hours?

00:38:59.300 --> 00:39:01.800 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Well, yeah, because
the adrenal glands basically

00:39:01.800 --> 00:39:03.570 align:middle line:90%
rule the 24-hour clock.

00:39:03.570 --> 00:39:07.260 align:middle line:84%
And so you really need to be
testing the adrenal hormones

00:39:07.260 --> 00:39:10.650 align:middle line:84%
over a 24-hour period,
which you can't do at a lab.

00:39:10.650 --> 00:39:13.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, what if you
were nearly in an accident

00:39:13.140 --> 00:39:14.930 align:middle line:84%
before you arrived at
the lab, and you've

00:39:14.930 --> 00:39:16.680 align:middle line:84%
had some kind of adrenal
response to that?

00:39:16.680 --> 00:39:18.450 align:middle line:84%
You're going to get a
skewed reading even there.

00:39:18.450 --> 00:39:18.750 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: That's true.

00:39:18.750 --> 00:39:20.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or being
afraid of a needle, even.

00:39:20.240 --> 00:39:20.410 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:39:20.410 --> 00:39:22.170 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Right, that's true.

00:39:22.170 --> 00:39:22.970 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:39:22.970 --> 00:39:24.430 align:middle line:90%
So the bloodwork is helpful.

00:39:24.430 --> 00:39:27.720 align:middle line:84%
I always like to see them back
to back with the saliva test.

00:39:27.720 --> 00:39:32.070 align:middle line:84%
But if I had my choice, I would
have the 24-hour cortisol panel

00:39:32.070 --> 00:39:35.730 align:middle line:84%
and the DHEA panel, the two
adrenal stress hormones,

00:39:35.730 --> 00:39:37.920 align:middle line:84%
and the estrogen,
progesterone, and testosterone

00:39:37.920 --> 00:39:39.380 align:middle line:90%
done through the saliva.

00:39:39.380 --> 00:39:41.490 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's done in the
convenience of your home

00:39:41.490 --> 00:39:44.610 align:middle line:84%
because it's just a saliva
collection that you do at home.

00:39:44.610 --> 00:39:46.520 align:middle line:90%
So it's very simple.

00:39:46.520 --> 00:39:49.080 align:middle line:90%
It's very simple to perform.

00:39:49.080 --> 00:39:52.830 align:middle line:84%
And then a treatment plan
is made from the test.

00:39:52.830 --> 00:39:57.810 align:middle line:10%
And my focus is to help people,
obviously, feel better and be

00:39:57.810 --> 00:40:00.990 align:middle line:10%
symptom free, but
really, more than that,

00:40:00.990 --> 00:40:04.230 align:middle line:10%
my focus is to help
people not need anything,

00:40:04.230 --> 00:40:06.540 align:middle line:10%
to get them to the point
where-- and it takes a while,

00:40:06.540 --> 00:40:10.020 align:middle line:10%
because everybody has
a different timeline.

00:40:10.020 --> 00:40:13.020 align:middle line:84%
It's certainly not going
to be a couple of weeks.

00:40:13.020 --> 00:40:15.530 align:middle line:84%
For most people, ti's going to
be about 18 months, actually.

00:40:15.530 --> 00:40:16.405 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, really?

00:40:16.405 --> 00:40:18.200 align:middle line:84%
Before they start seeing
long-term effects?

00:40:18.200 --> 00:40:20.570 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: They'll start
feeling better more quickly.

00:40:20.570 --> 00:40:23.600 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, you know,
when you're done,

00:40:23.600 --> 00:40:25.700 align:middle line:90%
it usually takes a lot longer.

00:40:25.700 --> 00:40:29.480 align:middle line:84%
But you know, I like to
use the dietary approach.

00:40:29.480 --> 00:40:30.560 align:middle line:90%
That's really important.

00:40:30.560 --> 00:40:32.660 align:middle line:84%
Like I said before,
when people walk away

00:40:32.660 --> 00:40:35.840 align:middle line:84%
and they're done with you, then
that's what they're left with.

00:40:35.840 --> 00:40:39.720 align:middle line:84%
And then they know how to
treat themselves with food.

00:40:39.720 --> 00:40:44.300 align:middle line:84%
And then I utilize certain
customized adrenal and female

00:40:44.300 --> 00:40:47.960 align:middle line:84%
and male hormone precursor
creams, liposomal creams,

00:40:47.960 --> 00:40:49.130 align:middle line:90%
that are made specifically.

00:40:49.130 --> 00:40:51.030 align:middle line:84%
These are nonprescription,
by the way.

00:40:51.030 --> 00:40:52.422 align:middle line:90%
These are not compounded--

00:40:52.422 --> 00:40:53.630 align:middle line:90%
pharmacy compounded products.

00:40:53.630 --> 00:40:54.650 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Oh, I was
wondering about that,

00:40:54.650 --> 00:40:56.600 align:middle line:10%
because another route
that a lot of people

00:40:56.600 --> 00:40:59.630 align:middle line:10%
take after they do their
panels is some practitioners

00:40:59.630 --> 00:41:02.030 align:middle line:10%
or doctors or OBGYNs
will have people

00:41:02.030 --> 00:41:04.460 align:middle line:10%
go on either
pharmaceutical hormones,

00:41:04.460 --> 00:41:06.428 align:middle line:10%
or they have them
go on bioidenticals.

00:41:06.428 --> 00:41:08.720 align:middle line:84%
But one thing I've noticed
about the bioidenticals that

00:41:08.720 --> 00:41:12.440 align:middle line:84%
are compounded is if you're not
under some pretty strict care

00:41:12.440 --> 00:41:14.450 align:middle line:84%
in terms of being
tested regularly,

00:41:14.450 --> 00:41:16.550 align:middle line:84%
you can throw your
hormones way out of balance

00:41:16.550 --> 00:41:20.760 align:middle line:84%
quickly with bioidenticals, just
like pharmaceuticals, right?

00:41:20.760 --> 00:41:21.560 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah.

00:41:21.560 --> 00:41:23.390 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a bioidentical
choice is a better

00:41:23.390 --> 00:41:25.190 align:middle line:84%
choice than the
pharmaceuticals, obviously,

00:41:25.190 --> 00:41:28.910 align:middle line:84%
because it's better
quality, and it matches

00:41:28.910 --> 00:41:31.490 align:middle line:90%
more what the body is making.

00:41:31.490 --> 00:41:34.340 align:middle line:84%
And if you take synthetic
estrogens, like Premarin,

00:41:34.340 --> 00:41:38.090 align:middle line:84%
for instance, you've got 23
different estrogens that are

00:41:38.090 --> 00:41:40.880 align:middle line:90%
available in the horse urine.

00:41:40.880 --> 00:41:43.500 align:middle line:84%
And the woman's body
has three estrogens.

00:41:43.500 --> 00:41:45.410 align:middle line:90%
So what happens to the other 20?

00:41:45.410 --> 00:41:48.740 align:middle line:84%
This is one of the reasons
there are so many, I think,

00:41:48.740 --> 00:41:50.720 align:middle line:90%
hormonal cancers.

00:41:50.720 --> 00:41:51.577 align:middle line:90%
But anyway--

00:41:51.577 --> 00:41:53.660 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So if you're
going to do one of the two,

00:41:53.660 --> 00:41:55.422 align:middle line:84%
the bioidenticals
are a better choice.

00:41:55.422 --> 00:41:57.380 align:middle line:84%
And that's what Suzanne
Somers and all her work

00:41:57.380 --> 00:41:58.960 align:middle line:90%
was about is that.

00:41:58.960 --> 00:42:01.340 align:middle line:84%
But I also know women who've
gotten in trouble with them.

00:42:01.340 --> 00:42:04.130 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: Yes, because
they do have a tendency

00:42:04.130 --> 00:42:05.360 align:middle line:90%
to be high potency.

00:42:05.360 --> 00:42:07.820 align:middle line:84%
The other problem with
them is that they are not

00:42:07.820 --> 00:42:10.550 align:middle line:90%
transdermally liposomal.

00:42:10.550 --> 00:42:13.130 align:middle line:84%
They're not actually
produced in a way

00:42:13.130 --> 00:42:16.250 align:middle line:84%
that they don't cause
buildup in the body.

00:42:16.250 --> 00:42:20.640 align:middle line:84%
And so the lab that I use,
they are aware of all that.

00:42:20.640 --> 00:42:23.690 align:middle line:84%
And so they have a
special liposomal method

00:42:23.690 --> 00:42:26.030 align:middle line:84%
that they use where they
attach a phospholipid

00:42:26.030 --> 00:42:30.800 align:middle line:84%
to the active ingredient, and
it creates 100 layer lipid--

00:42:30.800 --> 00:42:34.160 align:middle line:84%
100 lipid layer which allows
it to get into the cell

00:42:34.160 --> 00:42:36.650 align:middle line:84%
membrane and into
the bloodstream.

00:42:36.650 --> 00:42:38.057 align:middle line:90%
It bypasses the digestive tract.

00:42:38.057 --> 00:42:39.890 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: So there no
toxicity, essentially.

00:42:39.890 --> 00:42:40.180 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Right.

00:42:40.180 --> 00:42:41.170 align:middle line:90%
There's no buildup.

00:42:41.170 --> 00:42:41.970 align:middle line:90%
There's no buildup.

00:42:41.970 --> 00:42:42.710 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:42:42.710 --> 00:42:43.250 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah.

00:42:43.250 --> 00:42:45.440 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so you say
this is over-the-counter?

00:42:45.440 --> 00:42:46.790 align:middle line:10%
People can get these
over the counter?

00:42:46.790 --> 00:42:47.195 align:middle line:10%
>>THOMPSON: Right.

00:42:47.195 --> 00:42:49.028 align:middle line:10%
Well, you have to go
through a practitioner,

00:42:49.028 --> 00:42:51.320 align:middle line:10%
but it doesn't have to be
a medical prescription.

00:42:51.320 --> 00:42:52.830 align:middle line:84%
Well, I mean, it's not
a medical procedure.

00:42:52.830 --> 00:42:54.247 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So what
kind of pharmacy

00:42:54.247 --> 00:42:56.240 align:middle line:84%
distributes these
or dispenses these?

00:42:56.240 --> 00:42:59.210 align:middle line:10%
>>THOMPSON: There is a lab
in Carlsbad, California.

00:42:59.210 --> 00:43:00.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:43:00.010 --> 00:43:01.190 align:middle line:90%
So you go through that lab?

00:43:01.190 --> 00:43:01.430 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah.

00:43:01.430 --> 00:43:02.990 align:middle line:84%
And they actually
do the testing,

00:43:02.990 --> 00:43:06.368 align:middle line:84%
and then they actually custom
make the creams as well.

00:43:06.368 --> 00:43:08.660 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: So if a woman is
listening to this right now,

00:43:08.660 --> 00:43:11.000 align:middle line:10%
and she's out there
on her own, she's

00:43:11.000 --> 00:43:13.040 align:middle line:10%
done with allopathic
medicine-- maybe

00:43:13.040 --> 00:43:14.960 align:middle line:10%
she got burned by the
bioidentical thing

00:43:14.960 --> 00:43:17.300 align:middle line:10%
and wants to give it a
try and maybe doesn't even

00:43:17.300 --> 00:43:19.610 align:middle line:10%
have the funds to do the
full panels of testing

00:43:19.610 --> 00:43:20.600 align:middle line:10%
and everything.

00:43:20.600 --> 00:43:22.200 align:middle line:90%
What does she do?

00:43:22.200 --> 00:43:24.050 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: So the
first thing comes back

00:43:24.050 --> 00:43:26.783 align:middle line:84%
to the information I
gave to the teenage girl

00:43:26.783 --> 00:43:28.700 align:middle line:84%
in the beginning of our
conversation, which is

00:43:28.700 --> 00:43:30.440 align:middle line:90%
get the blood sugar imbalance.

00:43:30.440 --> 00:43:32.300 align:middle line:90%
Get rid of the wine every night.

00:43:32.300 --> 00:43:34.070 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't cut it.

00:43:34.070 --> 00:43:36.150 align:middle line:90%
Get rid of the chocolate.

00:43:36.150 --> 00:43:40.520 align:middle line:84%
And just do the due
diligence with diet.

00:43:40.520 --> 00:43:44.840 align:middle line:84%
Eat five small meals a day,
at least three proteins a day.

00:43:44.840 --> 00:43:48.310 align:middle line:84%
Drink half your body
weight in ounces in water.

00:43:48.310 --> 00:43:50.720 align:middle line:84%
If you're a 130-pound woman,
you drink about 2 quarts

00:43:50.720 --> 00:43:52.460 align:middle line:90%
of water a day.

00:43:52.460 --> 00:43:54.950 align:middle line:10%
And have physical activity.

00:43:54.950 --> 00:43:57.380 align:middle line:10%
Do something, whether
it be yoga or walking

00:43:57.380 --> 00:43:59.990 align:middle line:10%
or regular aerobic activity.

00:43:59.990 --> 00:44:02.990 align:middle line:10%
And do that which
brings you peace.

00:44:02.990 --> 00:44:05.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And happiness
and genuine joy,

00:44:05.150 --> 00:44:07.700 align:middle line:84%
which has to do with
connectivity with others.

00:44:07.700 --> 00:44:09.950 align:middle line:84%
And that has to do
with oxytocin, right?

00:44:09.950 --> 00:44:13.040 align:middle line:10%
From the time we're born
through the hugging process

00:44:13.040 --> 00:44:16.490 align:middle line:10%
with other people, it produces
oxytocin, all of these things

00:44:16.490 --> 00:44:18.120 align:middle line:10%
that have to do with community.

00:44:18.120 --> 00:44:21.530 align:middle line:84%
And before we get to
oxytocin, OK, what about-- can

00:44:21.530 --> 00:44:23.390 align:middle line:84%
they go to-- can they
call this lab and say,

00:44:23.390 --> 00:44:25.557 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to have some
of those hormone creams?

00:44:25.557 --> 00:44:27.890 align:middle line:84%
Can they do that, or do you
have to have a practitioner,

00:44:27.890 --> 00:44:28.690 align:middle line:90%
as you said?

00:44:28.690 --> 00:44:30.190 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: They
could call the lab,

00:44:30.190 --> 00:44:32.790 align:middle line:84%
and the lab could probably
refer them to a practitioner.

00:44:32.790 --> 00:44:34.248 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: And then
the practitioner

00:44:34.248 --> 00:44:35.930 align:middle line:10%
could write up
something for them.

00:44:35.930 --> 00:44:36.170 align:middle line:10%
OK.

00:44:36.170 --> 00:44:37.740 align:middle line:10%
And it's not terribly expensive?

00:44:37.740 --> 00:44:39.975 align:middle line:10%
I'm just trying to look
at someone taking it

00:44:39.975 --> 00:44:40.850 align:middle line:10%
into their own hands.

00:44:40.850 --> 00:44:42.308 align:middle line:10%
How could they do
this effectively?

00:44:42.308 --> 00:44:45.207 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: I think
a cream is about $70.

00:44:45.207 --> 00:44:46.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And how
long does that last?

00:44:46.790 --> 00:44:49.280 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: It depends,
because in the beginning,

00:44:49.280 --> 00:44:51.470 align:middle line:84%
it's usually a quarter of
a teaspoon, twice a day.

00:44:51.470 --> 00:44:55.040 align:middle line:84%
And that's about
a month's supply.

00:44:55.040 --> 00:44:58.520 align:middle line:84%
But like I said
before, the idea is

00:44:58.520 --> 00:45:01.820 align:middle line:84%
to strengthen the body so
you need less and less.

00:45:01.820 --> 00:45:05.630 align:middle line:84%
For instance, I've been on
creams for 13, 14 years.

00:45:05.630 --> 00:45:09.470 align:middle line:84%
And I'm still using the same
cream I had seven months ago

00:45:09.470 --> 00:45:11.540 align:middle line:90%
because I need less and less.

00:45:11.540 --> 00:45:13.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, very good point.

00:45:13.050 --> 00:45:14.508 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: So
yeah, at that point,

00:45:14.508 --> 00:45:15.930 align:middle line:90%
it's not expensive anymore.

00:45:15.930 --> 00:45:18.210 align:middle line:84%
I think most hormones
or brain chemical

00:45:18.210 --> 00:45:20.290 align:middle line:84%
programs are more
expensive in the beginning

00:45:20.290 --> 00:45:22.758 align:middle line:84%
because it's like a
front-loading thing.

00:45:22.758 --> 00:45:24.300 align:middle line:84%
